Cell.Data: Enable or disable a button. There are up to 8 buttons enumerated by 1 to 8. The button 1 corresponds to bit 0 and etc. A 0 disables the button and a 1 enables it.
Enable or disable the wind measurement. A 0 disables the wind measurement and a 1 enables it. Note, that if the wind measurement is enabled, the button 8 functionality will be disabled.

Enable or disable a relay. There are up to 8 relays enumerated by 1 to 8. The relay 1 corresponds to bit 0 and etc. A 0 disables the relay and a 1 enables it. Please note, that if a shutter is enabled, it doesn't matter that the relays are disabled here.

Cell.ss:Data:
Enable or disable a shutter. There are up to 4 shutter enumerated by 1 to 4. The shutter 1 corresponds to bit 0 and etc. A 0 disables the shutter and a 1 enables it. If a shutter is enabled, the used relays can not be controlled by single relay actions!
Bit 0: Enable shutter 1 and disable relay 1 and 2 to be controlled external. Bit 1: Enable shutter 2 and disable relay 3 and 4 to be controlled external. Bit 2: Enable shutter 3 and disable relay 5 and 6 to be controlled external. Bit 3: Enable shutter 4 and disable relay 7 and 8 to be controlled external.

Cell.Data: Enable or disable a relay event. There are up to 8 relay enumerated by 1 to 8. The relay 1 corresponds to bit 0 and etc. A 0 disables the event and a 1 enables it.

Enable or disable a shutter event. There are up to 4 shutter enumerated by 1 to 4. The shutter 1 corresponds to bit 0 and etc. A 0 disables the event and a 1 enables it. Note, that the shutter must be enabled.
A monostable relay is activated by using the switching current. The value is given as pwm duty cycle value (3-400).
A monostable relay is holded in active state by using the holding current. The value is given as pwm duty cycle value (3-400).
The zone which the node belongs to.
The sub-zone which the node belongs to.
The zone to which the button event belongs to (255 means all zones).
The sub-zone to which the button event belongs to (255 means all sub-zones).
The zone to which the relay event belongs to (255 means all zones).
The sub-zone to which the relay event belongs to (255 means all sub-zones).
The zone to which the shutter event belongs to (255 means all zones).
The sub-zone to which the shutter event belongs to (255 means all sub-zones).
The zone to which the wind event belongs to (255 means all zones).
The sub-zone to which the wind event belongs to (255 means all sub-zones).
Max. up-time (drive time from bottom to top) in 0.1s as 16-bit value. Shutter 1 is at the lower address and the other shutters follow.
Max. down-time (drive time from top to bottom) in 0.1s as 16-bit value. Shutter 1 is at the lower address and the other shutters follow.
Max. turn-time (turn 90°) in 0.1s as 16-bit value. Shutter 1 is at the lower address and the other shutters follow.
Log id (stream id) for logging functionality
